(122, 'David', 'Ruben (Piqtoukun)', NULL, NULL, 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=126', NULL, NULL),
(123, 'Adolf', 'Ryszka', NULL, 'Ryszka came to Vancouver in 1976 to participate in the Vancouver International Stone Sculpture Symposium in Van Dusen Gardens. An solo exhibition of his work was held at the Centre for Polish Sculpture in 1994. He said in his statement, \"I don\'t believe in verbal declarations. I believe in wisdom and suffering, self-sacrifice and love, modesty and kindness.\" -Vancouver Intl. Stone Sculpture Symposium catalogue', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=127', NULL, NULL),
(124, 'R. H.', 'Savery', NULL, 'Savery designed the setting for the fountain.', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=128', NULL, NULL),
(125, 'Ted', 'Sebastian', NULL, NULL, 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=129', NULL, NULL),
(126, NULL, 'See-wit', NULL, NULL, 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=130', NULL, NULL),
(127, 'Douglas', 'Senft', 'http://www.douglassenft.com', 'Senft has been a practicing sculptor since 1972 when he graduated with honours from the Vancouver School of Art.  He has done numerous public commissions in Canada and internationally. Since 1990 Senft has been designing and fabricating welded steel furniture and architectural elements and accessories. He teaches sculpture at North island College in Courtenay, BC and lives and works in Cumberland.', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=131', NULL, NULL),
(128, 'Jack', 'Shadbolt', NULL, 'Young Jack Shadbolt came to BC with his family in 1912 and settled in Victoria.  He studied in New York, London, and Paris, and taught at the Vancouver School of Art from 1938-1966, with time out during the war years in London. In 1966 he became a full-time painter and is one of the best known of the Vancouver modernists. In his work he explored the relationship between organic form and the pure energy of expression.  He exhibited nationally and internationally and published several books on painting., Act of Art (1981) and In Search of Form (1961). Shadbolt died in November 1998 at 89.', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=132', NULL, NULL),
(129, 'George Thornton', 'Sharp', NULL, 'Sharp was born in England in 1880. He was a founding partner of Thompson, Perwick, Pratt and Partners who designed many of the buildings at the University of BC.', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=133', NULL, NULL),
(130, 'Vern', 'Simpson', NULL, 'Simpson was a secondary school teacher from 1968-1988.  His vividly coloured landscape paintings are influenced by his frequent trips to Mexico and also by his love of the islands on the BC coast where he lives.  He has work in a number of corporate and public collections.', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=134', NULL, NULL),
(131, 'Gordon', 'Smith', NULL, NULL, 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=135', NULL, NULL),
(132, 'Joanna', 'Staniszkis', NULL, 'Staniszkis studied in Poland and at the Art Institute of Chicago and worked towards a career in interior design. She became interested in weaving and began working with designers and architects to create weavings and tapestries for their buildings. She researched antique tapestries and contemporary art-forms of other cultures for durable materials and different techniques. She has taught at the University of British Columbia and in 1981 she received the Saidye Bronfman Award for Craft.', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=136', NULL, NULL),
(133, 'Volker', 'Steigemann', NULL, 'Steigemann was born in Bavaria in 1958. His brother is also a sculptor and his grandfather is an artist and goldsmith. Steigemann came to Canada as an adult to see the wild country. At the time of the City Shapes sculpture festival, he lived on Cortes Island.', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=137', NULL, NULL),
(134, 'Arthur (Art)', 'Sterritt', NULL, 'Master carver Arthur Sterritt is a Gitksan from \'Ksan in the Upper Skeena River region.', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=138', NULL, NULL),
(135, NULL, 'Stonecoat Industries', NULL, 'Stonecoat Industries Limited is a B.C.-based company established in 1981.', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=139', NULL, NULL),
(136, 'Alan', 'Storey', 'http://alanstorey.net/', 'Alan Storey attended the University of Victoria and lives and works in Vancouver. His first major work was the Pendulum in the atrium of the HSBC Building on Georgia. His work often references industrial and mechanical processes. He has exhibited extensively since 1982 including solo exhibitions at the Western Front, Contemporary Art Gallery and Or Gallery in Vancouver and the 49th Parallel in NYC (1990), the Power Plant in Toronto (1990),  Indiana State University Gallery, Bloomington (1995), and the Centre Culturel Canadian, Paris, France in 2000. His work has also shown internationally in group exhibitions.  Storey has completed a number of public commissions in Canada and the US.', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=140', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ImageDisplay.aspx?AreaId=140&ImageId=529', NULL),
(137, 'Jiro', 'Sugawara', NULL, NULL, 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=141', NULL, NULL),
(138, 'Kiyoshi', 'Takahashi', NULL, NULL, 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=142', NULL, NULL),
(139, NULL, 'The Pier Group', NULL, NULL, 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=143', NULL, NULL),
(140, 'Patricia', 'Thomas', NULL, 'Patricia and Lionel Thomas worked on a number of artworks together including the mosaic for the Vancouver Public Library (no longer existing).', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=144', NULL, NULL),
(141, 'Lionel', 'Thomas', NULL, 'Lionel Thomas was born in Toronto in 1915 and studied at a number of schools including Ontario College of Art, Hans Hofmann School of Fine Arts, Provincetown, Mass; California School of Fine Arts, SF. He was an instructor at the School of Architecture, UBC, from 1950-59,  and Assoc. Professor in  Fine Arts until 1981. He exhibited extensively in Canada and internationally during the 1950s-70s including the Montreal Museum of Fine Arts, Hart House, Toronto, Grand Central Galleries, NY, the National Gallery of Canada, the Sao Paulo Biennial (1954), Seoul, Korea, and many more. In later life he  explored a fervent interest in astronomy and outer space.', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=145', NULL, NULL),
(142, 'Tommy', 'Tompkins', NULL, NULL, 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=146', NULL, NULL),
(143, 'Alan', 'Tregebov', NULL, 'Alan Tregebov lives and works in Toronto where he teaches at the School of Architecture at the University of Toronto. He has worked as a city planner and, as a member of Jurecka Lobko Tregebov Architects, has designed and renovated a number of public and private spaces in Canada and internationally.', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=147', NULL, NULL),
(144, 'Richard', 'Tetrault', 'www.richard-tetrault.ca', 'Richard Tetrault is a Canadian born artist based in Vancouver, Canada. His studio work includes painting, mixed media work and relief prints.  Tetrault explores the shifting dynamics of the urban landscape. He has participated in more than fifty solo and group exhibitions, and is represented in both public and private collections worldwide. As a muralist and educator, Tetrault has directed projects with artists, community members and students in locations ranging from Cuba, Mexico and Argentina to other parts of Canada and the United States. Recent projects include the six-story mural, Through the Eye of the Raven, (2010) River of Crows (2011) The Russian Hall (2009) and Community Walls/Community Voices (2003-04), all situated in Vancouver. He is a recipient of the City of Vancouver Mayor’s Art Award in 2008.', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=148', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ImageDisplay.aspx?AreaId=148&ImageId=530', NULL),
(145, 'Henry', 'Tsang', NULL, 'Born in Hong Kong and raised in Vancouver, Henry Tsang is an artist and curator and has taught at Emily Carr Institute of Art and Design in Vancouver.  He has exhibited in Canada and internationally in Newcastle-upon-Tyne, England (1993), New Delhi, India (1997), and Leipzig, Germany (1997). He has organized exhibitions that explore culture and art, including Self Not Whole at the Chinese Cultural Centre, Vancouver, 1991; Racy Sexy, Chinese Cultural Centre, 1993; and City at the End of Time: Hong Kong 1997 w/Scott McFarlane, multiple venues. Welcome to the Land of Light is his first permanent public art work though he has participated in several temporary projects.  He has published essays in art magazines internationally.', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=149', NULL, NULL),
(146, 'George', 'Tsutakawa', NULL, 'Tsutakawa was born on George Washington\'s birthday and was therefore named George. At age 7 he was sent to live in Japan and this strongly influenced his aesthetic which blends eastern and western ideas and forms.  He returned to Seattle in 1927 when he decided to become an artist. He studied under Alexander Archipenko and became friends with Mark Tobey and Morris Graves. When WWII began he was drafted and his family business was confiscated. After the war he returned to school and his art career.  He created over 60 fountains in North America and Japan during his career. He taught at the University of Washington from 1947-1976 when he retired.', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=150', NULL, NULL),
(147, 'Susan', 'Ockwell', NULL, 'Susan Ockwell worked for Busby + Associates Architects 1997 and Peter Cardew Architects in 1996. Uncoverings was her first public art work, in collaboration with Jill Anholt.', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=151', NULL, NULL),
(148, 'Dominique', 'Valade', NULL, 'Solo Exhibitions: 1998 St. Jerome, Quebec; 1996 Landscapes, Vertical Gallery, Laval, Quebec; 1994 Seeds and disseminations, CIRCA, ontreal, Quebec; 1991, Lachine Museum, Lachine, Quebec; A breach in the enclosure, the Gallery, Three-Rivers, Quebec.', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=152', NULL, NULL),
