(178, 'Sally', 'Gregson', NULL, 'Gregson attended the University of British Columbia and received her BFA at the University of Oregon. She also studied at the New School of Art in Toronto and informally at the Heatherly School in London and the Artists Workshop in Toronto as well as with Herbert Siebner in Victoria. She has worked as an illustrator at the Royal Ontario Museum and an art teacher in pubic schools and at Capilano College in North Vancouver. Her work is in the collections of the Canada Council Art Bank, Imperial Oil (Calgary), and the University of Toronto, among others.', 'https://covapp.vancouver.ca/PublicArtRegistry/ArtistDetail.aspx?FromArtistIndex=False&ArtistId=183', NULL, NULL),
